info.title: FHIR R4 Practitioner Resource

Practitioner.description: A person with a  formal responsibility in the provisioning of healthcare or related services

active.description: Whether this practitioner's record is in active use.

address.description: Address(es) of the practitioner that are not role specific (typically home address)

birthDate.description: The date of birth for the practitioner.

communication.description: A language the practitioner can use in patient communication.

identifier.description: An identifier that applies to this person in this role.

implicitRules.description: A set of rules under which this content was created

language.description: The base language in which the resource is written.

name.description: The name(s) associated with the practitioner.

telecom.description: A contact detail for the practitioner, e.g. a telephone number or an email address.

text.description: Text summary of the resource, for human interpretation

identifier.description: An identifier for this qualification for the practitioner

issuer.description: Organization that regulates and issues the qualification

period.description: Period during which the qualification is valid

PractitionerRole.description: Roles/organizations the practitioner is associated with

active.description: Whether this practitioner role record is in active use.

code.description: Roles which this practitioner is authorized to perform for the organization.

endpoint.description: Technical endpoints providing access to services operated for the practitioner with this role.

healthcareService.description: The list of healthcare services that this worker provides for this role's Organization/Location(s).

identifier.description: Business Identifiers that are specific to a role/location.

implicitRules.description: A set of rules under which this content was created

language.description: The base language in which the resource is written.

location.description: The location(s) at which this practitioner provides care.

organization.description: The organization where the Practitioner performs the roles associated.

period.description: The period during which the practitioner is authorized to perform in these role(s)

practitioner.description: Practitioner that is able to provide the defined services for the organization.

telecom.description: Contact details that are specific to the role/location/service.

text.description: Text summary of the resource, for human interpretation

availableEndTime.description: Closing time of day (ignored if allDay = true)

availableStartTime.description: Opening time of day (ignored if allDay = true)

daysOfWeek.description: mon | tue | wed | thu | fri | sat | sun

description.description: Reason presented to the user explaining why time not available

during.description: Service not available from this date

city.description: The name of the city, town, suburb, village or other community or delivery center.

country.description: Country - a nation as commonly understood or generally accepted.

district.description: The name of the administrative area (county).

line.description: Street name, number, direction & P.O. Box etc.

period.description: Time period when address was/is in use.

postalCode.description: A postal code designating a region defined by the postal service.

coding.description: A reference to a code defined by a terminology system.

text.description: Plain text representation of the concept

implicitRules.description: A set of rules under which this content was created

language.description: The base language in which the resource is written.

url.description: Source of the definition for the extension code - a logical name or a URL.

period.description: Time period during which identifier is/was valid for use.

system.description: The namespace for the identifier value

lastUpdated.description: When the resource last changed - e.g. when the version changed.

profile.description: Profiles this resource claims to conform to

security.description: Security Labels applied to this resource

source.description: Identifies where the resource comes from

period.description: Indicates the period of time when this name was valid for the named person.

prefix.description: Parts that come before the name

suffix.description: Parts that come after the name

text.description: Text representation of the full name

use.description: Identifies the purpose for this name.

contentType.description: Mime type of the content, with charset etc.

creation.description: The date that the attachment was first created.

data.description: The actual data of the attachment - a sequence of bytes, base64 encoded.

hash.description: The calculated hash of the data using SHA-1. Represented using base64.

language.description: The human language of the content. The value can be any valid value according to BCP 47.

size.description: The number of bytes of data that make up this attachment (before base64 encoding, if that is done).

title.description: A label or set of text to display in place of the data.

url.description: A location where the data can be accessed.

period.description: Time period when the contact point was/is in use.

rank.description: Specify preferred order of use (1 = highest)

system.description: phone | fax | email | pager | url | sms | other

use.description: Identifies the purpose for the contact point.

div.description: The actual narrative content, a stripped down version of XHTML.

code.description: Symbol in syntax defined by the system

display.description: A representation of the meaning of the code in the system, following the rules of the system.

system.description: The identification of the code system that defines the meaning of the symbol in the code.

userSelected.description: If this coding was chosen directly by the user

version.description: Version of the system - if relevant

end.description: End time with inclusive boundary, if not ongoing

start.description: The start of the period. The boundary is inclusive.

identifier.description: Logical reference, when literal reference is not known

reference.description: Literal reference, Relative, internal or absolute URL
